Commentary Text: Thakur to Pooran, out Caught by Dhoni!! Gone! They are making massive inroads in this game. That was a short ball, Pooran looks to pull and manages an inner edge for it to be taken by the keeper. Big wicket as Pooran is known to run away with a game. Three quick strikes have dented Punjab's chances big time. That was a shortish delivery and Pooran I guess was a little early into the shot. The keeper moved a little to his right and took it easily. Thakur went up and the umpire didn't have any doubts. Pooran c Dhoni b Thakur 2(6)

Commentary Text: Ravi Bishnoi to Ruturaj Gaikwad, no run, There's the wicket. Hang on! Gaikwad is not walking back. The umpires are checking if it is a clean catch. The soft signal is OUT. The third umpire has a look and goes in favour of the batsman. Rahul cannot believe it. He has a word with both umpires. They tell him to get on with the game. Kumble is on his feet in the dugout wanting a word with the fourth umpire I guess. The question is whether there was enough conclusive evidence to overturn the onfield call? Flighted outside off, Gaikwad slices the drive towards backward point, Mandeep dives forward and grasps it close to the ground. But looked like some part of the ball was touching the grass, it was not conclusive enough and that's why Kings XI are not happy
